Most of the &quot;final quest&quot; newbie items have been about the same as the gnome Necro staff. That book is pretty uber for a level 12ish player.<br>
<br>
By the way, these quests aren't all that easy. They take time to do. In most cases, you'll level faster than you'll get the quest items, so you'll be fighting greens to complete the quests.<br>
I've been playing an SK, and decided that the DE bone armor quests would be fun to get. After two weeks of doing nothing but hunting for the items needed, I'm still in need of a few pieces, and I've leveled to the point where all the creatures are green. Not to mention that every twink I run across tells me my armor sucks, and I shouldn't waste my time.<br>
<br>
These newbie quests were designed to give new players (and some old players) something to do at low levels. The problem is, all newbie players are more interested in gaining levels than spending a huge amount of time collecting items for a quest that they'll get no exp from.<br>
These items should be all be able to be obtained by level 12, and luck shouldn't be a huge factor. Im my opinion, these quests were dsigned for the right levels, but the items needed are far too rare in most cases.  <p><center>
